    "translation":{"eng":"Seeing the sorrowful condition of the living beings, Nitāi has brought the holy name from Vraja. This nāma Lord Śiva chants with his five mouths (so sweet is this harināma), This nāma Lord Brahmā chants with his four mouths (so sweet is this harināma). This nāma Nārada chants while playing his vīṇā (so sweet is this harināma). By simply chanting an ābhasa (mere semblance) of this nāma, Ajāmila went to Vaikuṇṭha. Bhaktivinoda says, “Continously chanting this holy name, let us go to Vraja!”"}}
